From : {bold}Sascha 'SieGeL' Pfalz{nobold} <siegel@siegel.in-berlin.de>
{p} {p}
Hi!
{p} {p}
Just a few comments on the new AIO GUI.
{p} {p}
It is very slow when running on a 16 Bit screen, scrolling down is a pain,
as it scrolls pixel by pixel, no chance to jump-scroll down.
{p} {p}
It looks more like a Windows GUI rather than an Amiga GUI, why not either
coding it as a standard MUI application or just switch to HTML ? HTML would
be really the best, as it is able to look great on better equipped amiga
whilst it won't loose much of the graphical optics when running on lower
Amigas.
{p} {p}
If the current GUI is used, please insert a better navigation bar, maybe all
buttons of the main window should be placed as buttons on bottom of the
window.
{p} {p}
However I really would prefer using HTML for the future.
{p} {p}
Just my $0.02 ;)
{p} {p}
And HAPPY CHRISTMAS TO THE AIO TEAM!
{p} {p}
Regards,
{p} {p}
Sascha 'SieGeL' Pfalz
{p} {p}
{italic}As with all new things not everyone is going to like it and yes it
seems you don't Sascha. Well regarding it running slowly it really depends
on how far you are pushing your Amiga, if you are expect to get the
full benifits from the new GUI using the great new 256 colours on a
basic Amiga then i'll tell you now it just won't work. I suggest you
turn down the screen colours on under powered Amigas. The above letter
says its fast so who knows whats going on?!
{p} {p}
Although MUI is very good and I couldn't live without it everything
done using MUI has that now stale MUI look which doesn't change from
program to program and really I don't see any benifits of using MUI.
This new GUI gets across AIO in a much better way and the cosmetics
of something are only for first impressions, it should really be the
content of AIO you should worry about.
{p} {p}
Currently HTML is not really an option. At the moment there are many
magazines around and not alot stand out from the crowd, to many games
only magazines, to many online/html magazines which I see boring and
plain. AIO is hopefully different and this GUI makes it special and
different to all the other clone magazines. I think this is a strong
point of AIO and I hope most of you would agree.
{p} {p}
Add your $0.02 anytime, feel free to encourage us or flame us, thats
the only way we'll improve.{noitalic}
